              sidebar:
                "[What is Solarpunk?](https://wiki.slrpnk.net/articles:whatissolarpunk)\n\n[A SolarPunk Manifesto](https://wiki.slrpnk.net/articles:manifesto)\n\n**Basic Rules:**\n- **be constructive**: there is no need of another internet space full of competition, negativity, rage etc.;\n- **no bigotry**, including racism, sexism, ableism, transphobia, homophobia or xenophobia;\n- **be empathic**: empathy is more rebellious than a middle finger;\n- **no porn and no gore**: let's keep this place easy to manage;\n- **no ads / spamming / flooding**, we don't want to buy/consume your commodified ideas;\n- **occasional self-promotion** by active members is fine.\n\n[Quick-start guide to Lemmy](https://wiki.slrpnk.net/lemmy)\n\nFor any community related question or to just test some function: [!meta@slrpnk.net](https://slrpnk.net/c/meta)\n\nTry our [Photon](https://photon.slrpnk.net/) &amp; [Alexandrite](https://alexandrite.slrpnk.net/) frontends.\n\nOr try our [lightweight UI](https://old.slrpnk.net/) and [Voyager mobile UI](https://voyager.slrpnk.net/).\n\nAll accounts also work with [XMPP chat](https://joinjabber.org/) automatically incl. our [Movim](https://movim.slrpnk.net/) client.\n\nIf you need to jointly brainstorm on your next Solarpunk text, try our [Etherpad](https://pads.slrpnk.net/).\n\nAnd don't miss [our Wiki](https://wiki.slrpnk.net/).\n\n[You can also donate towards the running costs of this instance](https://contribute.f-hub.org/?project=1).",
